# A Very Small Example Paper

Author: Revisica Demo

## Introduction

This paper studies a very important problem and it is obviously useful for many applications.
We will prove a theorem very quickly and the explanation is not very precise.

## Main Result

Let $f(x) = x^2$. We claim that

$$
\int_0^1 x^2 \, dx = \frac{1}{2}.
$$

Therefore, the average value of $x^2$ on $[0,1]$ is also $1/2$.

Now define

$$
g(x) = \frac{1}{x-1}.
$$

This function is continuous on $[0,1]$ so we can safely integrate it on this interval.

## Conclusion

We have shown the theorem and every step is straightforward.
